## ðŸ” CLI Quick Reference (AWS CLI)

> Assumes `aws` CLI configured and `--region` set or provided.

**Create VPC**
```bash
aws ec2 create-vpc --cidr-block 10.0.0.0/16 --tag-specifications 'ResourceType=vpc,Tags=[{Key=Name,Value=MyVPC}]'

CREATE SUBNETS:
aws ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id <VPC_ID> --cidr-block 10.0.1.0/24 --availability-zone <AZ>
aws ec2 create-subnet --vpc-id <VPC_ID> --cidr-block 10.0.2.0/24 --availability-zone <AZ>

CREATE & ATTACH IGW:
aws ec2 create-internet-gateway --tag-specifications 'ResourceType=internet-gateway,Tags=[{Key=Name,Value=MyIGW}]'
aws ec2 attach-internet-gateway --internet-gateway-id <IGW_ID> --vpc-id <VPC_ID>

CREATE NAT GATEWAY:
aws ec2 allocate-address --domain vpc        # returns AllocationId
aws ec2 create-nat-gateway --subnet-id <PUBLIC_SUBNET_ID> --allocation-id <ALLOC_ID>

CREATE ROUTE TABLES AND ROUTES:
aws ec2 create-route-table --vpc-id <VPC_ID>      # create PublicRT
aws ec2 create-route --route-table-id <PUBLICRT_ID> --destination-cidr-block 0.0.0.0/0 --gateway-id <IGW_ID>

aws ec2 create-route-table --vpc-id <VPC_ID>      # create PrivateRT
aws ec2 create-route --route-table-id <PRIVATERT_ID> --destination-cidr-block 0.0.0.0/0 --nat-gateway-id <NAT_ID>

(Use aws ec2 associate-route-table to associate tables to subnets.)

